<div class="grid_6">
  <article class="clearfix">
    <h3>Randy Bailey</h3>
    <h4>Co-owner &amp; Carpenter, too!</h4>
    <figure>
      <img src="/images/about/randy.jpg" alt="Randy Bailey">
    </figure>
    <p>My lifelong passion for building began as a kid growing up in upstate New York. Our family of 5 kids inherited all my great uncle's tools and set up "shop" in the front yard. I've been building things since I can remember.</p>
    <p>After working in residential remodeling, custom home building and with a Boulder architectural firm, I started BW Construction in 1989.</p>
    <p>I love remodeling because no two projects are alike. Complex and creative problem solving is both my expertise and what I do for fun.  I work with our clients to craft their project scope to meet both their dreams and their budget. My extensive experience in construction means I am an expert in value engineering, helping you maximize the satisfaction of your project.</p>
    <p>If I am not building for others, I'm creating something at home, or remodeling one of the tree houses I have built. I also love to ski, bike, or play in the outdoors. I've enjoyed sharing my love of carpentry with my daughters Nicki and Savi, and have taught them the essential carpentry technique that "if it doesn't work, wiggle it!"</p>
  </article>
  
  <article class="clearfix">
    <h3>Scott Dresser</h3>
    <h4>Lead Carpenter</h4>
    <figure>
      <img src="/images/about/scott.jpg" alt="Scott Dresser">
    </figure>
    <p>I have been a Lead Carpenter with BW Construction for over 15 years. An important reason I perform this work is the gratification I get daily by helping BW customers realize their remodeling goals. I also have the pleasure of making lasting friends along the way with our clients and their families. I am a task and detail-oriented manager who treats each BW project as I would my own. I am proud to work with a network of seasoned and talented professionals to make your project the very best it can be.</p>
    <p>Another reason I do this work is that it fits my active lifestyle. In my spare time I can usually be found working on my own home, biking, hiking, skiing or playing hockey. I also enjoy music, gardening, and our wonderful Colorado outdoors. I am a certified instructor for the National Outdoor Leadership School and a Wilderness First Responder.</p>
  </article>
  
  <article class="clearfix">
    <h3>Darren Klinefeter</h3>
    <h4>Lead Carpenter</h4>
    <figure>
      <img src="/images/about/darren.jpg" alt="Darren Klinefeter">
    </figure>
    <p>I have worked with BW since 2002. The greatest enjoyment I get is establishing a rapport and relationship with clients in order to fine tune projects with their interests, tastes and needs in mind.  I have a focused eye for detail and strive to show this in my projects.<p>
    <p>My interests outside of work are enjoying time with my daughters, wife and dog, as well as a wide variety of outdoor activities including: climbing, hiking, skiing, biking, camping, and canoeing. I also love wine. I do know my wines!</p>
  </article>
